ive reduction of psychology to neuroscience, which vindicates both the scientific legitimacy and the theoretical indispensability of psychology. This account is illustrated by several empirical examples borrowed from contemporary neuroscience.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aMind and body. 0aNeurosciencesxPhilosophy. 0aPhilosophy of mind. 0aPsychologyxPhilosophy. 4aErkenntnistheorie. 4aPhilosophie. 4aPsychologie. 7aPHILOSOPHY / History & Surveys / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z978311023857008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Philosophy 2000-2014 (EN)z978311023848808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Philosophy 2000 - 2014z9783110636949oZDB-23-GPH08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruyterteBook Package De Gruyter Ontos 2002-2012z978311033122608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruyterteBook Paket De Gruyter Ontos 2002-2012z9783110331219oZDB-23-DON0 cprintz978311032225540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311032262040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110322620423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110322620/original  a978-3-11-023848-8  DGBA Backlist Philosophy 2000-2014 (EN)c2000d2014  a978-3-11-023857-0  DGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1c2000d2014  a978-3-11-033122-6  eBook Package De Gruyter Ontos 2002-2012c2002d2012  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DONc2002d2012  aZDB-23-GPHc2000d2014